=====================================
  HOW TO RUN ALL CABCONNECT APPS
=====================================


═════════════════════════════════════
  ONE-TIME SETUP
═════════════════════════════════════

1. Install Node.js (LTS)
   Download: https://nodejs.org/

2. Install MongoDB Community Server
   Download: https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community
   During install, keep "Install MongoDB as a Service" checked.

3. Verify MongoDB is running:
   mongod --version

   If mongod is not recognized, add MongoDB to PATH:
   C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\<version>\bin
   Example: C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\7.0\bin

   Optional: open the Mongo shell (mongosh)
   mongosh

   If mongosh is not recognized, add it to PATH:
   C:\Program Files\mongosh\mongosh-<version>-win32-x64\bin
   Example: C:\Program Files\mongosh\mongosh-2.6.0-win32-x64\bin

4. Install Expo CLI globally (for mobile apps):
   npm install -g expo-cli

5. Install Expo Go on your phone (Android / iOS) for testing mobile apps.


═════════════════════════════════════
  ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
═════════════════════════════════════

Backend (.env in cabconnect-backend-main):
   PORT=5000                                        # optional, defaults to 5000
   MONGODB_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/ridehailing  # optional, defaults to this

Passenger App (.env in cabconnect-passenger-app):
   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://<your-ip>:5000        # optional, defaults to remote server
   EXPO_PUBLIC_GEOAPIFY_API_KEY=your_key            # for maps
   EXPO_PUBLIC_DIRECTIONS_API_KEY=your_key          # optional, Google Directions

Driver App (.env in cabconnect-driver-app):
   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://<your-ip>:5000        # optional, defaults to remote server
   EXPO_PUBLIC_GEOAPIFY_API_KEY=your_key            # for maps
   EXPO_PUBLIC_DIRECTIONS_API_KEY=your_key          # optional, Google Directions

   Tip: Copy .env.example to .env and fill in values.
   Tip: Use your local IP (not localhost) so mobile devices can reach the backend.


═════════════════════════════════════
  DAILY RUN
═════════════════════════════════════

Start MongoDB (run PowerShell as Admin):
   net start MongoDB


─────────────────────────────────────
  1. BACKEND SERVER
─────────────────────────────────────

   cd d:\Projects\08_CC\cabconnect-apps\cabconnect-backend-main
  
  

   Server runs at: http://localhost:5000
   Health check:   http://localhost:5000/health

   Available scripts:
     npm run dev    → development with hot-reload (ts-node-dev)
     npm run build  → compile TypeScript to dist/
     npm start      → run compiled build (node dist/index.js)


─────────────────────────────────────
  2. PASSENGER APP (Expo / React Native)
─────────────────────────────────────

   cd d:\Projects\08_CC\cabconnect-apps\cabconnect-passenger-app
   npm install
   npm start

   This launches the Expo dev server. Then:
     • Press  a  → open on Android emulator / Expo Go
     • Press  i  → open on iOS simulator (macOS only)
     • Press  w  → open in web browser
     • Scan the QR code with Expo Go on your phone

   Available scripts:
     npm start       → expo start (default)
     npm run android → expo run:android
     npm run ios     → expo run:ios
     npm run web     → expo start --web
     npm run lint    → expo lint


