═════════════════════════════════════
  RECOMMENDED STARTUP ORDER
═════════════════════════════════════

   1. MongoDB       (net start MongoDB)
   2. Backend       (npm run dev)
   3. Passenger App (npm start) — in a separate terminal
   4. Driver App    (npm start) — in a separate terminal


═════════════════════════════════════
  TROUBLESHOOTING
═════════════════════════════════════

  • "mongod is not recognized"
    → Add MongoDB bin folder to your system PATH.

  • Mobile app can't reach backend
    → Use your machine's local IP (e.g. 192.168.x.x) instead of localhost in .env.
    → Make sure your phone and PC are on the same Wi-Fi network.
    → Check Windows Firewall isn't blocking port 5000.

  • Expo cache issues
    → Run: npx expo start --clear

  • Port 5000 already in use
    → Set a different PORT in backend .env, or kill the process using that port.